<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-2942] Inadvertent auto-commit when pre-fetching can cause message loss</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2942</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Before returning from KafkaConsumer.poll(), we update the consumed position and invoke poll(0) to send new fetches. In doing so, it is possible that an auto-commit is triggered which would commit the updated offsets which hasn&apos;t yet been returned. If the process then crashes before consuming the messages, there would be a gap in the delivery.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
